text: Nevada City (originally, Ustumah, a Nisenan Maidu village; later, Nevada, Deer Creek Dry Diggins, and Caldwell's Upper Store) is the county seat of Nevada County, California, United States. It is located northeast of Sacramento and 28 miles north of Auburn. At the 2020 census, the population was 3,152. ==References== Category:Cities in California Category:County seats in California Category:Nevada County, California Category:1856 establishments in California
